      <hedline>
        <hl1>Unemployment vs. Inflation</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diane Fovre letter on Louis Uchitelle's July 30 column on isue of labor cost inflation notes that bottom 40 percent of workes have seen little or no real wage increases during economic boom</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The column presented a fair and balanced look at the concept of the Nairu and the issue of labor cost inflation. The bottom 40 percent of workers, however, have seen little or no real wage increases during the economic ''boom.'' Why don't corporations cut profits so these laborers can participate in the prosperity? Moreover, these workers may be thrown out of their jobs in order to supposedly check inflation. So they are two-time losers.</p>
        <p>DIANE FORVE  Los Angeles, July 30</p>
      </block>
